references: The quantitative results of the contributions, comparing variations of our best-performing models against existing baselines, can be found in Table 1. We report recommendation performance metrics, including HitRatio@10 and NDCG@10, as well as fairness metrics. Our findings reveal that our models outperform standard MF in terms of performance and are on par with ProtoMF and ACF on both datasets. Additionally, our models successfully reduce the difference between the average rank for under- and over-represented groups, demonstrating improved fairness. Furthermore, they are more inclusive towards less popular items, as evidenced by the decrease in the average long-tail rank. Notably, while both k-filtering and the regularizer independently improve fairness, their combined effect amplifies these improvements, leading to the fairest outcomes.
